# URLs lychee should skip. One regex per line.
#
# Each entry below is a real, working link that lychee can't verify from
# CI — either because the host blocks unauthenticated scrapers (Medium,
# Fandom, Speedrun, Gitconnected), the URL requires GitHub login (user
# project boards), or it routinely times out under CI's network conditions.
# The links are useful to readers; lychee just can't confirm them.
#
# Add entries narrowly — anchor patterns to the URL host (`^https?://...`)
# so a stray path segment like `example.com/medium.com-review/` can't
# silently match. Comment the reason on the same line for traceability.

# GitHub user-scope project boards: 200 to logged-in users, 404 to scrapers.
^https?://github\.com/users/brendanbyrne/projects/

# Medium and Medium-family hosts: 403 anti-bot on all unauthenticated traffic.
^https?://([^/]+\.)?medium\.com/
^https?://levelup\.gitconnected\.com/

# Speedrun.com forums: 403 anti-bot.
^https?://www\.speedrun\.com/

# Fandom (Mario Kart Racing Wiki and friends): 403 anti-bot. Referenced
# from frontend/{public,dist}/images/README.md when those READMEs exist.
^https?://([^/]+\.)?mariokart\.fandom\.com/

# nx.dev/docs: routinely times out under GitHub Actions network conditions.
^https?://nx\.dev/docs/

# npmjs.com package pages: 403 anti-bot on unauthenticated traffic. Package
# existence is verifiable via the registry API (registry.npmjs.org), which
# does not bot-block; the package-page links are fine for human readers.
^https?://(www\.)?npmjs\.com/

# tanstack.com docs: pages respond in <200ms from a normal network but the
# GitHub Actions IP range gets silently dropped (Cloudflare anti-bot), so
# lychee times out. Same CI-only-unreachable pattern as nx.dev/docs above.
^https?://tanstack\.com/
